                             <div class="spotlight-title" id="section-3">ImageNow LifeCycle</div> 
                              <div class="spotlight-summary"> 
                                
                                    1)<b>Implementation </b> Performance and stability best practices begin during the initial implementation. A Perceptive Software Consultant will configure ImageNow for optimal performance, as well as provide knowledge transfer to the ImageNow administrator and DBA on best practices.
                                    <br />
                                    2) Initiate a preventative maintenance program.  This should include: 
                                    <p style="margin-left : 2em;">
                                        <br />    a) A database maintenance plan. 
                                        <br />    b) Checks in the <a href="{!$site.prefix}/articles/Support_Troubleshooting/Article-000014464?popup=true">Stability checklist for the ImageNow environment.</a> 
                                    </p>
                                    <br />
                                        3) Performing a <b><a href="{!$site.prefix}/articles/Support_Troubleshooting/Article-000011192?popup=true">baseline</a></b> measurement quantifies the performance of ImageNow in normal conditions. The numbers derived from the baseline can then     be used as a comparison when isolating slow performance issues. The baseline should be updated after:
                                    <p style="margin-left : 2em;">
                                        <br />    a)  An upgrade
                                        <br />    b)  The addition of another department or business process
                                        <br />    c)  The completion of a large back-scanning project 
                                    </p>
                                    <br />
                                    4) A <a href="https://www.perceptivesoftware.com/services/professional-services/environment-consulting.psi">health check </a> is a strategic,   global audit of your business processes and ImageNow architecture provided by Perceptive Software Professional Services. We review your current ImageNow solution(s) and make recommendations for improvements based on industry best practices. Additionally, a technical architect will measure current performance and make recommendations on configurations, maintenance, and architecture to ensure your ImageNow environment delivers the best performance based on your organization’s business needs. Health checks are recommended:<br />
                                    <p style="margin-left : 2em;">
                                        <br />    a)  As part of an upgrade
                                        <br />    b)  After a major system change. For example:
                                        <p style="margin-left : 4em;">
                                            <br />    i)  The addition of a large department.
                                            <br />    ii) A large addition of documents, either from a back-scanning project or from a conversion from another ECM system. 
                                        </p>
                                        <p style="margin-left : 2em;">
                                            <br />    c)  If not initiated by one of the events above, then at the following regular intervals:
                                            <p style="margin-left : 4em;">
                                                <br />    i)   Every 9-12 months for an enteprise deployment 
                                                <br />    ii)  Every 18-24 months for a medium deployment 
                                                <br />    iii) Every 24-36 months for a small deployment
                                            </p>
                                        </p>
                                        <br />    5) <b> Upgrades</b> Perceptive Software recommends upgrading whenever your ImageNow version falls more than 2   releases behind to take advantage of new functionality and the latest performance enhancements to the   software.
                                   </p>     
                                </div>
